tip.text: The portion was just right but was slightly overpriced. Would've expected a larger portion with the price. But keep in mind you are paying for the imported Spanish charshu and tonkotsu soup.
The Bari-Uma and Kara-Uma was delicious. The soup was rich and flavourful without being too "jelak", salty or oily. However the the boiled eggs were overcooked; the yolk was way too runny.
Pork belly ramen and tonkotsu curry ramen were good. Sake sashimi was amazing. The only comment is that the edamame should've been steamed/boiled longer cuz the texture is a bit hard.
The spicy dragon ramen was delicious. The broth is super flavourful and the charshu is delicious.
